Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
read_taf(25.10)                                                read_taf(25.10)

Name
       read_taf  -  Applies additional attribute data from Genus for the user-
       managed exchanges

Syntax
       read_taf

       [-help]

       [<filename> [-quiet]

       Applies additional attribute data from Genus for the  user-managed  ex-
       changes. It is not needed for managed exchanges after iSpatial (syn_opt
       -spatial)  from  Genus to Innovus or when using common-DB between Genus
       and Innovus. The 'taf' format is a private format between Genus and In-
       novus.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each read_taf parameter.

       <filename>
              Specifies the name of file to read.

              Data_type: string, required

       -quiet When -quite is specified, the tool does not give a summary.

              Data_type: bool, optional

